    • Method Detail

      • processLineData

        protected void processLineData(java.lang.String[] lineTokens)
        Processes an individual series of data values from a line imported from a File and adds them to the SystemObjects database. Because this is service data, individual services for existing routes will be created along with information about their days of operation, time periods, and path. A series of ServiceStops will be placed in each service which are the containers for all service-related data.
        Specified by:
        processLineData in class FileImport
        Parameters:
        lineTokens - array of String objects for each data value.

      • interpretPeriod

        private Period interpretPeriod(java.lang.String dys,
                     java.lang.String tm)
        Interprets the period identifiers from an import file into a Period object. The default strings are
        "WK" for weekdays, "SA" for Saturdays, "SU" FOR Sundays;
        "EA" for early (0:00 - 6:00), "AM" for morning rush (6:00 - 9:00), "BS" for mid-day (9:00 - 15:00), "PM" for evening rush (15:00 - 18:00), and "NI' for late hours (18:00 - 24:00 ).
        Parameters:
        dys - one of the default String specifiers for days, listed in the description
        tm - one of the default String specifiers for time periods, listed in the description
        Returns:
